<item>
            <title>[LU-19311] lnet: optionally allow link-local IPv6 addresses to be configured with LNet</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-19311</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Although link-local IPv6 addresses are limited in scope such that they can be used to communicate directly (L2-limited, i.e. can&apos;t go beyond router), they are automatically available and still may be used if it is ok to stay within the same L2 domain.&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Add an option which allows link-local IPv6 addresses to be used by LNet, but turn it off by default.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
